Question: How to have List Iterator start at a given index?:

A: You can use a for loop to iterate through the list until it reaches the index that was given.
public Iterator<E> iterator(int x ){
    Iterator<E> it = new ListIterator();
    for(int i = 0; i < x; i++){
        it.next();
    }
    return it;
}
